I’ve confirmed the main risk cluster is in `PresaleV5.sol` itself: initialization is missing, several lifecycle gates are defined but never enforced, and purchase functions trust external calls too loosely. I’m tracing variable usage now to separate hard exploits from owner-only misconfiguration.
